definitions.definition: A shallow deformation in the surface of an object, produced by an impact .
examples: The crash produced a dent in the left side of the car.

definitions.definition: ( figurative ) A minor effect made upon something.
A type of maize / corn with a relatively soft outer hull , and a soft type of starch that shrinks at maturity to leave an indentation in the surface of the kernel .
( by extension , informal ) A sudden negative change, such as loss , damage , weakening , consumption or diminution , especially one produced by an external force, event or action
examples: That purchase put a bit of a dent in my wallet.
